maneuvers.narrative: Start out going southeast on E 1st St toward S Los Angeles St.
Turn left onto N Los Angeles St.
Merge onto US-101 S.
Merge onto I-10 E via EXIT 1D on the left toward San Bernardino/I-10 E (Crossing into Arizona).
Merge onto South Mountain Fwy/AZ-202 Loop N via EXIT 138 toward AZ-202 Loop S.
South Mountain Fwy/AZ-202 Loop N becomes E Pecos Rd.
Merge onto I-10 E/US-87 S via EXIT 53 toward Tucson (Passing through New Mexico, then crossing into Texas).
Take the I-35 N exit, EXIT 570, on the left toward Austin.
Merge onto I-35 N via the ramp on the left toward US-281 N/Johnson City/Corpus Christi/I-37 S/US-281 S.
Take the I-410 S exit, EXIT 162.
Merge onto I-410 S via the ramp on the left.
Take EXIT 33 toward I-10/Houston/US-90/TX-130/San Antonio.
Keep left to take the I-10 E/TX-130 N/US-90 E ramp toward Houston/Seguin.
Merge onto I-10 E via the ramp on the left.
Keep left to take I-10 E toward Lake Charles (Crossing into Louisiana).
Merge onto I-12 E via EXIT 159 on the left toward Hammond.
I-12 E becomes I-10 E (Passing through Mississippi and Alabama, then crossing into Florida).
Merge onto I-75 S via EXIT 296A toward Tampa.
Keep left to take FL-91 S via EXIT 328 toward Orlando (Portions toll).
Take Florida's Turnpike (Portions toll) (Electronic toll collection only).
Stay straight to go onto Ronald Reagan Turnpike/FL-91 S. Continue to follow FL-91 S (Portions toll).
Take the FL-826 W exit toward I-95/US-441.
Merge onto I-95 S via the ramp on the left.
Take the NW 8th St exit, EXIT 3B, toward Port of Miami.
Stay straight to go onto NW 3rd Ct.
Turn left onto NW 5th St.
Turn right onto N Miami Ave.
Turn right onto NW 1St St.
Welcome to MIAMI, FL.
